# Real-time collaboration (peer-to-peer, WebRTC via Yjs / y-webrtc).
#
# Peers find each other through a signaling server (only SDP/ICE handshakes
# pass through it — never your manuscript or notes, which go directly
# peer-to-peer and can be end-to-end encrypted with a session passphrase).
#
# Leave unset to use y-webrtc's default public signaling servers. To run your
# own (recommended for reliability/privacy), set one or more comma-separated
# wss:// (or ws:// for local dev) URLs. A simple server ships with y-webrtc:
#   PORT=4444 node node_modules/y-webrtc/bin/server.js
#
# VITE_SIGNALING=wss://signaling.example.com
